item.description: A single flowering plant.

item.title: Senecio platylepis
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Annual herb less than 40cm tall. Only this single flowering plant observed. Previous weeks have seen very good rains.

item.title: Xanthium strumarium spp. agg.
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Growing along edge of Murray River.

item.title: Goodenia fascicularis
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Not especially silky, but all other characters point to Goodenia fascicularis, which has previously been observed in this area.

item.title: Sarcozona praecox
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Differentiate from co-existing Noon-flower by triangular cross-section of leaves, paler leaves that are often red-tinged, and flowers that do not ascend above leaves (in Noon-flower flowers sit above leaves).

item.title: Osteocarpum salsuginosum
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Growing near edge of Alectryon oleifolius tree. Not commonly encountered here. Fruit required to confidently differentiate from very similar Osteocarpum acropterum.

item.title: Silene apetala var. apetala
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Exotic annual herb, growing here less than 20cm tall near the base of Alectryon oleifolius subsp. canescens.

item.title: Rhodanthe stricta
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Single plant observed at this location, within 25 metres of Murray River bank. Rare plant across this landscape.

item.title: Fumaria bastardii
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Only a single, small patch of plants observed growing within 20 metres of Murray River bank.

item.title: Bulbine semibarbata
item.dc:creator: chrisl
item.description: Note the hair tufts at the base of stamens on the longer three filaments only. Bulbine alata has hair tufts at the base of each stamen.
